==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eleatic
<hw>E`le*at"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>eleaticus</ets>, from <ets>Elea</ets> (or <ets>Velia</ets>) in
Italy.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a certain school of Greek
philosophers who taught that the only certain science is that which owes
nothing to the senses, and all to the reason.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A philosopher of the Eleatic
school.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eleaticism</ent>⟦br⟧
